# DbAccounts — project knowledge

Cross-platform **PostgreSQL role maintenance** desktop app: manage clusters, batch-run role operations via **user-defined PostgreSQL functions** (not direct DDL in app).

## Product decisions (do not regress)

| Topic | Decision |
|-------|----------|
| UI shell | **Wails v2** + embedded WebView; frontend is vanilla HTML/CSS/JS in `frontend/` |
| DB driver | **pgx/v5**; direct **TCP** to `host:port` (no SSH tunnels in v1) |
| Secrets | **Never** store passwords in YAML; optional `connect_user` only. Auth: cluster `connect_user` → run-dialog user → `PGUSER`; password: non-empty dialog → `PGPASSWORD` → `~/.pgpass` → **empty** (trust / no password, like psql) |
| Role logic | App calls **call templates** with `${placeholder}` → `SELECT fn($1,...)` — real DDL/privileges live in **DB functions** on each cluster |
| Categories | Default `production` and `uat`; extensible in config YAML |
| DB function specs | User will provide real names/signatures; defaults in `config.example.yaml` are placeholders (`your_schema.*`) |

## Stack (current)

- Go module: `github.com/michalbartak/dbaccounts`
- Wails **v2.12.0** (CLI may auto-bump `go.mod` on `wails dev`)
- pgx v5, yaml.v3, google/uuid
- Bindings: `frontend/wailsjs/` — **auto-generated** by Wails; do not hand-edit; regenerate via `wails dev` / `wails build`

