## Layout

```
main.go, app.go           Wails entry + bindings
internal/config/          YAML persistence
internal/model/           Shared types + RunRequest
internal/calltemplate/    Call template parse/validate/SQL build (stdlib only)
internal/pg/              DSN, auth, Connect, CallFunction
internal/batch/           Concurrent executor
internal/commands/        Op validation + arg maps
internal/envimport/       PG* env import
frontend/                 UI (app.js uses backend())
sql/README.md             Docs for user's PostgreSQL functions
```

## Out of scope (v1)

SSH tunnels, encrypted config vault, audit log file, reading remote `pg_hba.conf`.

## Safety (implemented)

- Production badge + checkbox `confirmProduction` + extra confirm dialog
- Remove role: in-app `<dialog id="confirm-dialog">` (not `window.confirm()` — broken in Wails WebView)
- Password inputs masked; not written to config

## Pending / follow-ups

1. User may need different function signatures on server — adjust `call` templates and literals only in config (not app code) when possible.
2. Do **not** edit `.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` unless user explicitly asks.

## Package dependencies (avoid import cycles)

| Package | May import | Must not import |
|---------|------------|-----------------|
| `internal/model` | (stdlib only) | other `internal/*` |
| `internal/calltemplate` | stdlib | `config`, `pg`, `commands`, `batch` |
| `internal/config` | `model`, `calltemplate` | `pg` |
| `internal/pg` | `model`, `calltemplate`, pgx | `config` |
| `internal/commands` | `model`, `config` | — |

- Config validates templates via `calltemplate.ValidateCallTemplate`, not `pg`.
- **`internal/pg` tests must not import `internal/config`** (creates cycle: config → calltemplate ← pg test → config).
- Cross-package SQL tests: `commands` + `calltemplate`, or `calltemplate` alone.

## Tests & CI

- Run **`make test`** (or `go test ./...`) before committing.
- GitHub Actions: `.github/workflows/test.yml` on push/PR.
- When adding an operation: extend `AllowedPlaceholders`, `commands.BuildArgs`, defaults in `config/store.go`, tests in `calltemplate`, `commands`, `config`.

## Conventions when changing code

- Minimal diffs; match existing package layout and naming.
- JSON struct tags on model types for Wails (camelCase).
- After changing Go bindings, run `wails dev` or `wails build` to refresh `frontend/wailsjs/`.
- Comments only for non-obvious business rules.
